## Test Strategy

### Scenario Coverage
Each requirement scenario above maps to at least one test case:
- [ ] R1 scenarios → `test_[feature].py`
- [ ] R2 scenarios → `test_[feature].py`
- [ ] R3 scenarios → `test_[feature].py`
- [ ] S1 scenarios → `test_[feature].py`

### Regression Patterns
See `tasks/lessons.md` for full cross-cutting patterns. Common ones to consider:
- [ ] False positives — valid real-world data that looks like an invalid match
- [ ] Error handling at boundaries — invalid input produces a clear error, not a silent default
- [ ] Encoding edge cases — non-ASCII characters, BOM, composed vs decomposed Unicode

